				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: &quot;DieselGate&quot; possible huge fall of VW Group?
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1841231">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							The tech isn't the issue. I feel that people will remember &quot;VW cheated on emissions&quot;, not &quot;diesel cars cheated on emissions&quot;. I think the really interesting thing will be if this reverses the EPA's views on people &quot;jailbreaking&quot; their own vehicles:<br />
<br />
<a href="http://www.wired.com/2015/09/epa-opposes-rules-couldve-exposed-vws-cheating/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://www.wired.com/2015/09/epa-opp...-vws-cheating/</a><br />
<br />
This is a fairly large consumer issue because, as controls in a vehicle become computerized or linked to the onboard computer, they will only be able to be repaired by technicians authorized to access the onboard computer under a &quot;no tampering&quot; regulatory framework. Those will be dealership mechanics, who are bound by franchise agreements to use more expensive OEM parts, and it could spell the end of non-dealership repair shops.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<div class="cleardiv"></div>
		</div>
	</div>
